==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mitrailleuse
<hw>Mi`tra`illeuse"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>mitrailler</ets> to fire grapeshot, fr. <ets>mitraille</ets> old
iron, grapeshot, dim. of OF. <ets>mite</ets> a mite.]</ety>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A breech-loading machine gun consisting of a
number of barrels fitted together, so arranged that the barrels can be
fired simultaneously, or successively, and rapidly.</def>
<mark>[obsolescent]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mitral</ent>⟦br⟧
